# Portfolio layout — no horizontal overflow (permanent)

NEVER create horizontal scrollbars on the document. Always use `overflow-x: hidden` on `html` and `body`. Always use `box-sizing: border-box` on `*`, `*::before`, and `*::after`. Always use `100%` (or `max-width: 100%`) instead of `100vw` for full-width layouts so scrollbar gutter does not cause overflow.

All static pages (`index.html`, case studies, `design-system*.html`, `brand-identity.html`, etc.) must be fully usable at **375px**, **768px**, and **1440px** widths: no horizontal overflow on any element, no clipped critical content.

## Required global CSS pattern (every page)

```css
html, body {
  overflow-x: hidden;
  max-width: 100%;
}
*, *::before, *::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
```

Keep margin/preset resets compatible with the above (e.g. same selector or separate `*, *::before, *::after { margin: 0; padding: 0; }`).

## Implementation checklist

- **Containers:** `max-width: 100%`, `min-width: 0` on flex/grid children where needed.
- **Media:** `img`, `svg`, `video`: `max-width: 100%`; `height: auto` unless fixed intentionally inside a bounded box.
- **Tables:** Wide tables only inside a wrapper with `overflow-x: auto`, `max-width: 100%`, `min-width: 0` (e.g. `.table-scroll`, `.scroll-x`).
- **Grids:** default to **single column** on small viewports; avoid fixed multi-column min widths that exceed 375px.
- **Color / token rows:** use `flex-wrap: wrap` or responsive grid so swatches never force page width.
- **Avoid:** `100vw` on full-bleed sections; negative margins that pull content past the viewport; `white-space: nowrap` on long headings without `max-width` + truncation or wrapping.

No future change should reintroduce a horizontal scrollbar on `html`/`body`.
